## Constraints

- Every `public_interface` item must use domain vocabulary, not implementation jargon.
- ADR proposals are offered sparingly — only when all three conditions are met: hard to reverse, surprising without context, result of a real trade-off.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Preserve the original prompt structure and formatting.
- Handle missing variables gracefully (leave as-is or use default if specified).

